description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Clinical Coding Assistant to join our team at Mid and South Essex Foundation Trust based at Southend Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Coding Department analyse complex clinical information from patient records and translate this into a coded format in line with National Standards. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are seeking a self-motivated and driven individual to play a pivotal role in providing a high standard of support and administrative duties to the Clinical Coding Department. The post holder will be responsible for providing general assistance to the Clinical Coding Team through collecting medical records following patient discharge, tracking paper case notes, filing case notes and answering telephones as well as dealing with general office enquiries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Candidates will be expected to transport notes around the hospital using trolley’s and will be required to lift small boxes containing patient’s notes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will need excellent communication skills and be able to work on your own initiative and as part of a team. You must have excellent attention to detail and have accurate keyboard skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKaren WelhamJob titleClinical Coding Operational ManagerEmail addressKaren.welham@southend.nhs.ukTelephone number01702 385537&lt;/p&gt;
